1
00:00:12,553 --> 00:00:14,475
All right, let's talk about our D options.

2
00:00:14,575 --> 00:00:17,038
So D equals new construction.

3
00:00:17,058 --> 00:00:18,099
Correct.

4
00:00:18,499 --> 00:00:18,760
Okay.

5
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:22,684
Does that mean it's in a completely different space than the building today?

6
00:00:23,484 --> 00:00:25,487
It doesn't have to be in a complete difference.

7
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:29,711
It just means that everything that we're building at the end of the day is completely new.

8
00:00:29,731 --> 00:00:34,816
There will be no renovation associated with it, but it may be overlapping on the existing building.

9
00:00:34,836 --> 00:00:34,916
Sure.

10
00:00:35,843 --> 00:00:45,249
The MSBA has requirements if you're going to build new that would require us to separate the pool.

11
00:00:46,029 --> 00:00:53,693
Can you tell us what that means so that we can just sort of clear up the pool conversation as it relates to these options?

12
00:00:53,714 --> 00:00:54,194
Sure.

13
00:00:55,076 --> 00:01:02,505
So the pool, if we're going to build it new, has to be a separate standalone project and building from the high school building.

14
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:10,895
And so when I say a standalone project, what that means is that we actually have to go out and publicly advertise and procure

15
00:01:11,575 --> 00:01:17,619
a construction team for that project that could in theory be different than the one that is building the high school project.

16
00:01:17,919 --> 00:01:24,363
We also need to make sure that the building in terms of its operation is completely detached from the high school building itself.

17
00:01:24,403 --> 00:01:31,647
So that means a separate electrical service, a separate plumbing services that go to a pool which are considerable for a pool.

18
00:01:32,804 --> 00:01:38,166
And it just has to be fully removed and detached from the high school building itself.

19
00:01:38,946 --> 00:01:46,949
The other important thing to note about a separate pool building is that we actually have to approve any debt override for that pool building.

20
00:01:47,707 --> 00:01:50,670
as a separate vote from the high school project itself.

21
00:01:51,311 --> 00:02:03,262
They can be on the same ballot, but they have to be two separate questions so that the voters can weigh in on their support for the pool structure as separated from the high school structure.

22
00:02:03,602 --> 00:02:03,782
Great.

23
00:02:04,563 --> 00:02:07,204
The MSP will not cost share for the pool, is that correct?

24
00:02:07,244 --> 00:02:07,765
That is correct.

25
00:02:07,865 --> 00:02:09,225
Even a renovated pool.

26
00:02:09,245 --> 00:02:13,788
So this is a Medford only cost when we are talking about the pool.

27
00:02:14,088 --> 00:02:24,773
The reason this has a really high modular number, modular classroom number, and that's because some of this new building is sort of encroaching on the footprint of the current building, is that right?

28
00:02:25,173 --> 00:02:43,456
it is yes and so we did do that in a deliberate manner to say well if we tried to take the entirety of this building footprint and build it just on the parking lot and to have zero modulars with this type of approach what it would mean is that the building which is six stories just going from a flat plane six stories up

29
00:02:44,299 --> 00:02:48,042
we'd probably be having to add at least another story or two on top of that.

30
00:02:48,182 --> 00:02:50,664
And so it starts to become a very, very large building.

31
00:02:50,724 --> 00:03:00,130
And we heard that these extremely tall buildings are not desirable necessarily for students to be moving up and down through, even though it's not horizontally a long distance.

32
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:06,135
Trying to get up eight stories of stairs in the course of a school day is also a challenging ask for students.

33
00:03:07,015 --> 00:03:26,600
I'll also say the challenge, if we were to try to minimize or eliminate modulars with this site on the parking lot, is that there's a lot of programs at the high school that want to have street frontage down at the first floor, whether it's the main entrance of the high school, whether it is the CTE programs that have a retail component, the early education center.

34
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:36,108
And when we get that tight in terms of just building on the parking lot, we have a very limited amount of linear footage around the perimeter to have that sort of exterior site access.

35
00:03:36,589 --> 00:03:39,872
You have to fit a loading dock and receiving area in as well.

36
00:03:39,952 --> 00:03:43,876
So that will become extremely challenging to get so tight.

37
00:03:44,356 --> 00:03:51,323
And so that is why we extended out a little bit further towards and on top of the existing building footprint with this particular option.

38
00:03:51,843 --> 00:04:00,705
And the reason that the number of modular classrooms is so high is because we are impacting the B wing in this case, as well as a portion of the vocational wing.

39
00:04:00,965 --> 00:04:04,466
Relatively speaking, this I think was maybe the most expensive option.

40
00:04:04,546 --> 00:04:08,627
And so can you tell us, are there any other factors that are sort of driving that cost?

41
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:17,389
So there, when we think about the tall buildings in particular, there's a building code requirement that we have to address is called a high rise building.

42
00:04:17,809 --> 00:04:21,510
When we get above or less four stories, the five stories and above.

43
00:04:22,306 --> 00:04:36,116
which causes some increases in terms of the amount of infrastructure we need to put in the building both from like a smoke evacuation standpoint and making sure that the stairwells are reinforced from an overall nature.

44
00:04:36,136 --> 00:04:39,759
So you just think about building a high-rise building it becomes a little bit more expensive.

45
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:44,743
So there's a premium in terms of the building construction cost when we go tall with options such as this.

46
00:04:45,923 --> 00:04:54,607
Really the reason why this one became the most expensive is because it does have all these compounding reasons that you started to cover in terms of driving the cost up.

47
00:04:54,707 --> 00:04:58,549
It does have that synthetic turf field over the top of parking.

48
00:04:59,309 --> 00:05:06,593
We can always look at going back to surface parking with this option and doing whatever remains in terms of surface field down below.

49
00:05:07,734 --> 00:05:14,060
as one way of trying to adjust the cost or work the cost of this one so it's not quite as impactful.

50
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:25,772
The other one, the other aspect of this that's driving up is the modular classroom quantity and that is just directly due to that impact again over the top of the existing vocational wing, the southern portion.

51
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:27,334
as well as the B wing.

52
00:05:27,834 --> 00:05:37,765
And so while we could make the building tighter and try to avoid those existing footprints, we're going to again create maybe an environment that is not ideal from an educational perspective.

